WEBVTT

00:07.107 --> 00:09.141
- Previously on <i>the affair...</i>

00:09.143 --> 00:12.745
- I had no idea she was married
when I first met her.

00:12.747 --> 00:15.748
She seemed like
the loneliest girl in the world.

00:15.750 --> 00:20.352
- I was wondering if you--
you still needed a hand.

00:20.354 --> 00:22.221
- I'm noah.
- Cole.

00:22.223 --> 00:23.489
- Which dress?
- That one.

00:23.491 --> 00:24.656
- I think I'm gonna wear
this one.

00:24.658 --> 00:26.425
- This is harry, my agent.

00:26.427 --> 00:28.093
- So bruce tells me
that you're working on something

00:28.095 --> 00:29.495
New this summer?

00:29.497 --> 00:31.230
- Well, I haven't really gotten
too far with it.

00:31.232 --> 00:33.232
- Excuse me, sir.
You ordered whiskey?

00:33.234 --> 00:34.633
- Was she flirting with you?

00:34.635 --> 00:36.502
- You know, you really shouldn't
smoke that here.

00:36.504 --> 00:38.370
- Okay.
Where should we go?

00:38.372 --> 00:40.239
- How is any of this relevant
to what happened?

00:40.241 --> 00:41.774
- Trying to figure out if anyone
might have had a motive

00:41.776 --> 00:42.775
To kill this fellow.

00:42.777 --> 00:44.243
- I thought it was an accident.

00:44.245 --> 00:45.511
- How much longer
is this gonna take?

00:45.513 --> 00:47.112
- I just have
a few more questions.

00:47.114 --> 00:48.447
- I was sure
I'd never see him again.

00:48.449 --> 00:50.249
I remember you.

00:50.251 --> 00:52.117
- I was wondering when
we'd run into each other again.

00:52.119 --> 00:53.819
I'd like to keep talking
with you.

00:53.821 --> 00:56.722
- Got a call about a catering
job tonight if anyone wants it.

00:56.724 --> 00:59.391
- You're that poor little girl
who lost her baby, aren't you?

00:59.393 --> 01:00.826
- Do you wanna get out of here?

01:00.828 --> 01:03.062
There's this hypothesis in
theoretical physics.

01:03.064 --> 01:05.264
Your true life continues as is,
unchanged.

01:05.266 --> 01:06.732
But at the moment of decision,

01:06.734 --> 01:09.535
A new life splits off
into a parallel universe.

01:09.537 --> 01:11.837
- I really doubt it was anyone
at the party that ran him down.

01:11.839 --> 01:13.739
- So you think I'm barking up
the wrong tree?

01:13.741 --> 01:15.841
- I'll do anything to find out
what happened to him.

01:15.843 --> 01:17.109
I can't believe he's gone.

01:29.322 --> 01:32.458
- ♪ I was screaming
into the canyon ♪

01:32.460 --> 01:35.694
♪ at the moment of my death

01:35.696 --> 01:38.864
♪ the echo I created

01:38.866 --> 01:42.101
♪ outlasted my last breath

01:42.103 --> 01:45.337
♪ my voice,
it made an avalanche ♪

01:45.339 --> 01:48.507
♪ and buried a man
I never knew ♪

01:48.509 --> 01:50.242
♪ and when he died

01:50.244 --> 01:51.577
♪ his widowed bride

01:51.579 --> 01:54.213
♪ met your daddy
and they made you ♪

01:54.215 --> 01:56.181
♪ I have only one thing to do

01:56.183 --> 01:57.850
♪ and that's be the wave
that I am ♪

01:57.852 --> 02:01.386
♪ and then sink
back into the ocean ♪

